<div class="tw-foot p"><div class="fn" id="fn4"><p>Values are given as mean (5th and 95th percentiles). Frequencies are shown as <em>n</em> (%). DHA, docosahexaenoic acid; EPA, eicosapentaenoic acid. Body mass index (BMI) shown is before pregnancy. Smoking status is during pregnancy. Smoking data missing for 24 participants (13 in control group and 11 in DHA group). Birth weights are medians. Breastfeeding duration missing for 82 participants (48 in control group and 34 in DHA group). <em>P</em> values from <em>t</em>-test for continuous variables or χ<sup>2</sup>-test for categorical variables.</p></div></div></section></section><section id="sec2-1-2"><h4 class="pmc_sec_title">Modulation of DNA methylation profiles of imprinted genes IGF2 P3, IGF2 DMR, and H19 DMR by DHA supplementation.</h4>
<p><a href="#T3" class="usa-link">Table 3</a> shows CpG site-specific means of DNA methylation levels, which are means of the methylation percentages for the CpG sites, at <em>IGF2</em> promoter 3 (<em>IGF2</em> P3), <em>IGF2</em> DMR, and <em>H19</em> DMR at birth in the control and DHA groups. For <em>IGF2</em> DMR and <em>H19</em> DMR, the methylation level was close to the 50% expected for imprinted genes: full on one parental allele and absent on the other parental allele; <em>IGF2</em> DMR had a mean methylation level of 50.81% [95% confidence interval (CI): 50.05%, 51.57%] for the control group and 51.28% (95% CI: 50.52%, 52.03%) for the DHA group; <em>H19</em> DMR had a mean level of 54.95% (95% CI: 54.04%, 55.86%) for the control group and 54.72% (95% CI: 53.81%, 55.62%) for the DHA group (<a href="#T3" class="usa-link">Table 3</a>). The mean methylation level in <em>IGF2</em> P3 was 4.00% (95% CI: 3.49%, 4.51%) for the control group and 4.32% (95% CI: 3.82%, 4.83%) for the DHA group. However, there were no significant differences between the DHA and the control groups.</p>
